# Organic / Natural UI (scoped)

**Source of truth:** `design/design-system.md`

**Stack:** Jekyll — SCSS in `_sass/`, markup in `_includes/` and `_layouts/`. Map tokens to SCSS variables/mixins; match existing partials and skins. Do not add React/Tailwind unless the user requests a migration.

## When this applies

- Designing, styling, or refactoring visual UI
- User asks for design system / organic / natural look

**Do not apply** to `_config.yml`, content-only edits, analytics, build tooling, or non-visual work.

## Non-negotiables

- **Vibe:** Wabi-sabi — warm, soft, tactile; no sharp 90° corners or pure-black shadows
- **Colors:** `#FDFCF8` bg, `#2C2C24` fg, `#5D7052` primary, `#C18C5D` secondary, `#E6DCCD` accent, `#F0EBE5` muted, `#DED8CF` border, `#A85448` destructive
- **Typography:** Fraunces 600–800 (headings), Nunito or Quicksand (body)
- **Shapes:** `rounded-2xl`/`rounded-3xl` base; organic blobs via multi-value `border-radius` (e.g. `60% 40% 30% 70% / 60% 30% 70% 40%`)
- **Shadows:** Soft, tinted — moss `rgba(93,112,82,0.15)`, clay `rgba(193,140,93,0.2)` — never `#000` drop shadows
- **Texture:** Global grain/noise overlay ~3–4% opacity, `mix-blend-mode: multiply`
- **Motion:** Gentle `transition-all duration-300`–`500`; buttons `hover:scale-105` / `active:scale-95`; cards lift `hover:-translate-y-1`
- **A11y:** 48px touch targets; `focus-visible:ring-2` moss `#5D7052` with offset

## Components (SCSS mapping)

- **Buttons:** Pill (`border-radius: 9999px`); primary moss + pale mist text; outline terracotta 2px; ghost moss text + moss/10 hover
- **Cards:** `#FEFEFA` bg, timber border 50% opacity, `2rem` radius + asymmetric corner variants, moss soft shadow, noise layer
- **Inputs:** Pill, timber border, `rgba(255,255,255,0.5)` bg, moss focus ring
- **Nav:** Sticky floating pill, `rgba(255,255,255,0.7)` + backdrop blur, `rounded-full`

## Workflow

1. Read `_sass/` partials and active skin before editing
2. Plan: tokens → partials → includes
3. Use blob backgrounds, staggered grids, section tints (stone/sand/moss/terracotta) for depth — avoid generic Bootstrap polish
